a_Sidle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sara_Sidle\"}, {\"begin\": 155, \"end\": 160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.81507931835961e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The team stunned Australia and delivered the first-ever Olympic medal for the team and its Jewish forward, Levy.\", \"from\": 232, \"to\": 344, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 249, \"end\": 258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.539293450373435e-15, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According toThe Forward, the sport runs deep in the Levy family.\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Levy's great-grandfather,Louis Brabow, played professionally and famously weighed whether to play a match in New Zealand on Yom Kippur in 1937.\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 554, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 436, \"end\": 448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Babrow\", \"score\": 0.9999810499024745, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Louis Brabow\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Babrow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Babrow\"}, {\"begin\": 520, \"end\": 531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_league_team\", \"score\": 0.9616574796727133, \"rank\": 0.018333963606226775, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_league_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_league_team\"}, {\"begin\": 535, \"end\": 545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yom_